{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/react-native/atomic_structure/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Consisty","author":"Consisty System","siteUrl":"https://blog.consisty.com","comment":{"disqusShortName":"","utterances":"Consisty/Consisty.github.io"},"sponsor":{"buyMeACoffeeId":""}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"de7da269-f574-5e67-a195-4d6df05a0510","excerpt":"Why would to use Atomic structure? Let’s say a developer has a list of buttons used for the application , all in black background and white title color. They haven’t worked in the application in a while and need to come back to the application to add a new button with progress…","html":"<h2 id=\"why-would-to-use-atomic-structure\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#why-would-to-use-atomic-structure\" aria-label=\"why would to use atomic structure permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Why would to use Atomic structure?</h2>\n<p>Let’s say a developer has a list of buttons used for the application , all in black background and white title color. They haven’t worked in the application in a while and need to come back to the application to add a new button with progress. They could take a look at the buttons that already exist and customize one of them to get the result they desire or created new progress button. Also, decreases the inconsistency between component and view, repeated code and lack of style-guide component .</p>\n<h2 id=\"features\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#features\" aria-label=\"features permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Atomic design breaking down user interfaces into small and simple element.</li>\n<li>Improve consistency and complexity between components and view.</li>\n<li>Code is reuseable.</li>\n<li>Improve the readability, scalability and flexibility of your application code.</li>\n<li>Reduces development time.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"structure\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#structure\" aria-label=\"structure permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Structure</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 41.891891891891895%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;Atomic Structure&quot;\"\n        title=\"&quot;Atomic Structure&quot;\"\n        src=\"/static/6ac524b1d8d7221475561e030074f078/fcda8/atomic_structure_01.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6ac524b1d8d7221475561e030074f078/12f09/atomic_structure_01.png 148w,\n/static/6ac524b1d8d7221475561e030074f078/e4a3f/atomic_structure_01.png 295w,\n/static/6ac524b1d8d7221475561e030074f078/fcda8/atomic_structure_01.png 590w,\n/static/6ac524b1d8d7221475561e030074f078/f0551/atomic_structure_01.png 862w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>Atoms :</strong>\nAtoms is the smallest component . Which is used by context,globally or withine other components and in templates . Every components having many states. So easy to use for development.</p>\n<p><strong>Example:-</strong>\n<strong>Button</strong> is the single component having different states or options like size,enable or disable,haver,pressEvents etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Molecules :</strong>\nMolecules creates functionality using atoms and have own properties. Molecules is the <strong>combination of two or more atoms</strong>. Which don’t have any action or functionality by themselves. Reuse some of those component or begin to compose complex component.</p>\n<p><strong>Organisms :</strong>\nOrganisms are the <strong>combination of molecules that works together or even single atoms composed to elabrate interface</strong>. Organisms is the most of final shape of component to use . They are independent,reuseable,poratable in any content.</p>\n<p><strong>Templates :</strong>\nTemplates is becomes using the context of component . Templates create <strong>relationship between organisms and other components</strong> through the various components placement, set the positions and patterns of the pages.</p>\n<p><strong>Pages :</strong>\nPages are the <strong>navigate</strong> part in the application. Where the components are distributed in one template. Need to connect more than one templates. In this stage need to check efficiency of the design system to analyze all component are independent enough or need to split them in smaller element (part).</p>\n<p><strong>File Structure:</strong>\nHere is the file structure of Atomic Design.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 72.2972972972973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;File Structure&quot;\"\n        title=\"&quot;File Structure&quot;\"\n        src=\"/static/0c1d38e917ecc0e6476da68c3b047a5b/fcda8/file_structure_02.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0c1d38e917ecc0e6476da68c3b047a5b/12f09/file_structure_02.png 148w,\n/static/0c1d38e917ecc0e6476da68c3b047a5b/e4a3f/file_structure_02.png 295w,\n/static/0c1d38e917ecc0e6476da68c3b047a5b/fcda8/file_structure_02.png 590w,\n/static/0c1d38e917ecc0e6476da68c3b047a5b/efc66/file_structure_02.png 885w,\n/static/0c1d38e917ecc0e6476da68c3b047a5b/d6a46/file_structure_02.png 1008w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></br></p>\n<p>Created new src folder and atoms,molecules,organisms, screens are under the src folder. Screens is used instead of template and pages. If you would be use other element then can be split it in different component . If need to use navigation in project then create different folder for navigation and create navigation javascript file like <strong>StackNavigation.js, DrawerNavigation.js,BottomNavigation.js</strong> etc. So,code is reusable and very compatible for developer.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.70270270270271%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;atoms&quot;\"\n        title=\"&quot;atoms&quot;\"\n        src=\"/static/a303fc0ecafcc807f91e3cec7edd0bdf/fcda8/atoms_03.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a303fc0ecafcc807f91e3cec7edd0bdf/12f09/atoms_03.png 148w,\n/static/a303fc0ecafcc807f91e3cec7edd0bdf/e4a3f/atoms_03.png 295w,\n/static/a303fc0ecafcc807f91e3cec7edd0bdf/fcda8/atoms_03.png 590w,\n/static/a303fc0ecafcc807f91e3cec7edd0bdf/efc66/atoms_03.png 885w,\n/static/a303fc0ecafcc807f91e3cec7edd0bdf/98b29/atoms_03.png 937w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></br></p>\n<p>In the above project created <strong>ActionButton.js</strong> and other various button files in button folder and <strong>NormalText.js</strong> and other required text file for project created in text folder . Here can compose different component in atoms as per requirement of project. Also,apply style ,actions,states inline or using global context .</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.70270270270271%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;molecules&quot;\"\n        title=\"&quot;molecules&quot;\"\n        src=\"/static/d00ee5dfbfbef7d2a4faeb39937ed69d/fcda8/molecules_04.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d00ee5dfbfbef7d2a4faeb39937ed69d/12f09/molecules_04.png 148w,\n/static/d00ee5dfbfbef7d2a4faeb39937ed69d/e4a3f/molecules_04.png 295w,\n/static/d00ee5dfbfbef7d2a4faeb39937ed69d/fcda8/molecules_04.png 590w,\n/static/d00ee5dfbfbef7d2a4faeb39937ed69d/efc66/molecules_04.png 885w,\n/static/d00ee5dfbfbef7d2a4faeb39937ed69d/eafa0/molecules_04.png 939w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></br></p>\n<p>In molecules created EditTextBox.js file . To set the label for editTextBox used NormalText.js file from atoms .Used different states and global context. They have own set of action,style and integration of unit is independent in application. So that reducess developer efforts and easy to test code consistently and effectively.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.70270270270271%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;organisms&quot;\"\n        title=\"&quot;organisms&quot;\"\n        src=\"/static/037247855ebf0fdc370092fe0c5f75ea/fcda8/organisms_05.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/037247855ebf0fdc370092fe0c5f75ea/12f09/organisms_05.png 148w,\n/static/037247855ebf0fdc370092fe0c5f75ea/e4a3f/organisms_05.png 295w,\n/static/037247855ebf0fdc370092fe0c5f75ea/fcda8/organisms_05.png 590w,\n/static/037247855ebf0fdc370092fe0c5f75ea/efc66/organisms_05.png 885w,\n/static/037247855ebf0fdc370092fe0c5f75ea/dc616/organisms_05.png 933w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></br></p>\n<p>Organism folder contains combination of molecules and atoms . In above project create <strong>SearchSenderModel.js</strong> file by combination of <strong>EditTextBox.js</strong> from molecules and <strong>LoadingActionButton.js</strong> from atoms. Every component is independent. So, easy to do change request or resolve any bugs .</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 78.37837837837837%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;screens&quot;\"\n        title=\"&quot;screens&quot;\"\n        src=\"/static/8de564edbec11446825ce1c10001c647/fcda8/screens_06.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8de564edbec11446825ce1c10001c647/12f09/screens_06.png 148w,\n/static/8de564edbec11446825ce1c10001c647/e4a3f/screens_06.png 295w,\n/static/8de564edbec11446825ce1c10001c647/fcda8/screens_06.png 590w,\n/static/8de564edbec11446825ce1c10001c647/efc66/screens_06.png 885w,\n/static/8de564edbec11446825ce1c10001c647/82b28/screens_06.png 931w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></br></p>\n<p>Instead of templates and pages created Screens folder in project. In which created <strong>AtomicDesign.js</strong> screen for that composed <strong>SearchSenderModel.js</strong> from organisms and required some text file from atoms for mentioning label.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 72.2972972972973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"&quot;actual screens&quot;\"\n        title=\"&quot;actual screens&quot;\"\n        src=\"/static/19bfb37446c0b0b4aeea24270e22d7e2/fcda8/actual_screen_07.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/19bfb37446c0b0b4aeea24270e22d7e2/12f09/actual_screen_07.png 148w,\n/static/19bfb37446c0b0b4aeea24270e22d7e2/e4a3f/actual_screen_07.png 295w,\n/static/19bfb37446c0b0b4aeea24270e22d7e2/fcda8/actual_screen_07.png 590w,\n/static/19bfb37446c0b0b4aeea24270e22d7e2/efc66/actual_screen_07.png 885w,\n/static/19bfb37446c0b0b4aeea24270e22d7e2/c83ae/actual_screen_07.png 1180w,\n/static/19bfb37446c0b0b4aeea24270e22d7e2/3c492/actual_screen_07.png 1300w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></br></p>\n<p>Finally, got the output in which showing text and editbox with button. Applyed error message in red color using <strong>Formik and Yup</strong> packges by React . Button press event is used to show the error message if input is null or empty and provided input using <strong>TextInput</strong>. They uses various state , props and styles as per design. Some are used inline and some provides through global contex.</p>\n<h2 id=\"references\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>References</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@janelle.wg/atomic-design-pattern-how-to-structure-your-react-application-2bb4d9ca5f97#:~:text=The%20main%20purpose%20of%20following,lot%20more%20readable%20and%20modular\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Atomic Design Pattern</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/react_native\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Tutorial Points - react-native</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.awesome-react-native.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Awesome React Native</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Atomic Structure In React Native","date":"September 25, 2020","authorID":"3"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/react-native/atomic_structure/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/react-native/create_expo_project/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Create react native project with Expo","category":"React-Native","draft":false}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/react-native/swr_api_calling/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"SWR In React-Native Part1","category":"React-Native","draft":false}}}}}